title: Taylor Swift
description:
Taylor Alison Swift (born December 13, 1989) is an American country music singer-songwriter. Signed to the independent Big Machine Records label in 2006, Taylor made her debut on the U.S. Billboard country charts with the release of her debut single "Tim McGraw".

Her self-titled debut album was released in late 2006, and has since been certified triple platinum by the RIAA in the United States. As of June 21, 2008 the album has sold 3,021,703 copies in the U.S and it has produced five Top Ten singles on the U.S. Billboard Hot Country Songs, including two Number One singles with "Our Song" and "Should&#039;ve Said No"; all five of her singles have also reached Top 40 on the Billboard Hot 100. The album was re-issued in 2007 with a set of bonus tracks.
